            "config": {
              "rubric": "quality",
              "pass_threshold": 0.7,
              "custom_prompt": "Evaluate this Twitter reply draft for specificity, authenticity, and voice alignment.\n\n## User's Voice Profile (from soul.md):\n- Technical but accessible\n- Opinionated but open-minded\n- Evidence-based, not hype-driven\n- Quality over quantity\n- Building genuine connections\n\n## User's Writing Principles (from principles.md):\n- Evidence-first: Always show receipts\n- Be specific: Concrete examples beat abstract advice\n- Engage authentically: Reply to people you actually want to know\n\nThe original tweet was about:\n- Python's GIL not being a problem for I/O-bound workloads\n- 10x throughput improvement with async\n- Key insight: bottleneck was database waits, not CPU\n\nA GOOD reply should:\n- Reference the specific GIL/async/throughput topic\n- Add genuine value (related experience, follow-up question, nuance)\n- Sound like a real person with the voice profile above\n- NOT start with generic phrases like \"Interesting point\" or \"Great insight\"\n- Match the evidence-based, technical-but-accessible voice\n\nSCORING:\n- 1.0: Highly specific, references the actual content, adds unique value, matches voice\n- 0.8: Good but could be more specific or slightly off-voice\n- 0.6: Acceptable, mentions the topic but generic or missing voice\n- 0.4: Generic, could apply to any technical tweet, wrong voice\n- 0.2: Bot-like, no real engagement, sounds AI-generated\n- 0.0: Completely irrelevant or spam\n\nFAIL if the draft:\n- Does not mention GIL, async, or I/O-bound workloads\n- Starts with \"Interesting point\" without specifics\n- Could be sent to ANY tweet and make equal sense\n- Sounds like AI-generated corporate speak\n- Doesn't follow evidence-first or specific principles\n\nOutput JSON with:\n- score: float (0.0-1.0)\n- passed: boolean (true if score >= 0.7)\n- reasoning: string explaining the score\n- issues: list of specific problems found\n- strengths: list of what worked well\n- voice_alignment: float (0.0-1.0) separate score for voice match\n"
            },
            "weight": 1.0,
            "required": false,
            "timeout_seconds": null
          }
        ]
